{%- comment -%}
  Header cart icon — dedicated section used ONLY as a Section Rendering
  API target from `assets/cart-drawer.js::refreshDrawer()`.

  Why a standalone section: the drawer's refreshDrawer fetches
  `/?sections=cart-drawer,header-cart-icon` after every qty change or
  ATC. The Section Rendering API requires the `sections` key to
  reference real section files; without this file the `header-cart-icon`
  response key was silently missing and the drawer fell through to a
  full cart.js fetch, round-tripping extra bytes on every update.

  The cart count pill that visually lives in sections/header.liquid is
  duplicated here — the JS swaps the inner textContent, not the node,
  so the visible header icon (rendered by sections/header.liquid) keeps
  its event listeners intact. Keeping this section tiny keeps the SRA
  response small (~200 bytes vs. the ~5 KB header.liquid would emit).

  NOT rendered on the storefront — it isn't in any template's section
  group. Shopify's SRA accepts orphan sections as long as the section
  file exists, which is the entire purpose here.
{%- endcomment -%}
<span
  class="kt-header__cart-count"
  aria-live="polite"
  aria-atomic="true"
  {% if cart.item_count == 0 %}style="display: none;"{% endif %}
>
  {{ cart.item_count }}
</span>

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Header cart icon",
  "tag": null,
  "settings": []
}
{% endschema %}
